# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears in the user interface of the
# application, guiding the user on what to expect after initiating a new plan
# within the software.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown 2026-06-16T14:42:36Z
#: osparc/product/quickStart/tis/ElectrodeSelector.js
msgid "        After pressing New Plan, three panels will be shown.      "
msgstr "Después de presionar Nuevo Plan, se mostrarán tres paneles."

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears in the user interface of a
# scientific simulation application during the setup phase, where users define
# parameters for an electrical stimulation experiment.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown 2026-06-16T14:42:38Z
#: osparc/product/quickStart/tis/ElectrodeSelector.js
msgid ""
"        In a first step, the relevant species, stimulation target, "
"electrode shapes, electrode dimensions and         potential electrode "
"locations (currently required to narrow down the huge exposure "
"configuration search space) are selected.      "
msgstr ""
"En un primer paso, se seleccionan las especies relevantes, el objetivo de "
"estimulación, las formas de los electrodos, las dimensiones de los "
"electrodos y las posibles ubicaciones de los electrodos (actualmente "
"necesarias para reducir el enorme espacio de búsqueda de configuraciones de "
"exposición)."

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears in the user interface of the
# application, guiding users on how to submit their configuration after
# setting up the simulation parameters.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown 2026-06-16T14:42:40Z
#: osparc/product/quickStart/tis/ElectrodeSelector.js
msgid ""
"        After finishing the set up, the big button on the top right will "
"turn blue and by clicking on it you will submit the configuration.      "
msgstr ""
"Después de terminar la configuración, el gran botón en la parte superior "
"derecha se volverá azul y al hacer clic en él, enviarás la configuración."

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears in the user interface of the
# application, guiding the user to proceed to the next step in the
# optimization process by clicking a button labeled 'Next'.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown 2026-06-16T14:42:41Z
#: osparc/product/quickStart/tis/ElectrodeSelector.js
msgid ""
"        Now the Arrow that says 'Next' can be pushed and the optimization "
"will immediately start.      "
msgstr ""
"Ahora se puede presionar la flecha que dice 'Siguiente' y la optimización "
"comenzará inmediatamente."

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears as a menu option in the application,
# allowing users to access tools for analyzing and visualizing simulation
# results after computations are complete.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown 2026-06-16T14:42:42Z
#: osparc/product/quickStart/tis/PostPro.js
msgid "Post Processing"
msgstr "Postprocesamiento"

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears in the user interface of a
# scientific simulation application, guiding users on how to explore and
# document optimal exposure parameters using interactive tools.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown 2026-06-16T14:42:43Z
#: osparc/product/quickStart/tis/PostPro.js
msgid ""
"        Based on extensive sweeping/optimization, a series of highly "
"performing exposure parameters are proposed for the         user to "
"interactively explore, using predefined quantification metrics and "
"visualizations. Identified         conditions-of-interest can be documented "
"and added to a report.      "
msgstr ""
"Basado en una extensa optimización, se proponen una serie de parámetros de "
"exposición de alto rendimiento para que el usuario los explore "
"interactivamente, utilizando métricas de cuantificación y visualizaciones "
"predefinidas. Las condiciones de interés identificadas pueden documentarse "
"y añadirse a un informe."

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears in the user interface of a
# scientific simulation application, specifically in the section where users
# analyze and visualize the results of electrode stimulation simulations.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown 2026-06-16T14:42:44Z
#: osparc/product/quickStart/tis/PostPro.js
msgid ""
"        These metrics are reported in the Post Processing analysis "
"environment for each electrode pair in the combination in         a sorted "
"tabular form that can be used to inspect the stimulation performances. By "
"clicking on each pair, slice views         of the maximum amplitude "
"modulation (MAP) within the head are produced.<br>        Pressing the "
"`Load` button on the right, the selected configuration will be loaded.      "
msgstr ""
"        Estas métricas se informan en el entorno de análisis de Post "
"Procesamiento para cada par de electrodos en la combinación en         una "
"forma tabular ordenada que se puede usar para inspeccionar los rendimientos "
"de estimulación. Al hacer clic en cada par, se producen vistas de "
"corte         de la modulación de amplitud máxima (MAP) dentro de la cabeza."
"<br>        Al presionar el botón `Cargar` a la derecha, se cargará la "
"configuración seleccionada.      "

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears in the user interface of a
# scientific simulation application, describing visualization and analysis
# features for electromagnetic field simulations within anatomical models.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown 2026-06-16T14:42:46Z
#: osparc/product/quickStart/tis/PostPro.js
msgid ""
"        Alternatively, slice views of the maximum interferential E-field "
"can also be visualized and synchronous with the MAP slices         to "
"assess safety-related aspects (e.g., field intensity in proximity of the "
"electrodes). These maps can be edited, thresholded,         and saved "
"offline for further inspection and analysis.<br>        An isosurface of "
"the TI stimulation distribution for the selected configuration can also be "
"visualized within the head anatomy for inspection.      "
msgstr ""
"Alternativamente, también se pueden visualizar vistas de corte del campo "
"eléctrico interferencial máximo y sincronizarlas con los cortes del MAP "
"para evaluar aspectos relacionados con la seguridad (por ejemplo, la "
"intensidad del campo en proximidad de los electrodos). Estos mapas se "
"pueden editar, umbralizar y guardar sin conexión para una inspección y "
"análisis posterior.<br>También se puede visualizar una isosuperficie de la "
"distribución de estimulación TI para la configuración seleccionada dentro "
"de la anatomía de la cabeza para su inspección."

# CTX-INTERPRETATION: This string appears in the user interface of a
# scientific simulation application, specifically in a section related to
# generating reports after completing an optimization procedure.
# CTX-VERSION: unknown 2026-06-16T14:42:48Z
#: osparc/product/quickStart/tis/PostPro.js
msgid ""
"        At the end of the optimization procedure, you can automatically "
"generate a report.<br>        It includes a summary of all the performance "
"metrics calculated for each electrode pair combination, and a detailed "
"performance report         of the optimized electrode configuration. The "
"report includes electrode placement, current intensities, performance "
"metrics, TI and maximum         high-frequency field distributions, "
"cumulative dose histograms and all the graphs generated in the post-pro "
"analysis tab.      "
msgstr ""
"Al final del procedimiento de optimización, puede generar automáticamente "
"un informe.<br>Incluye un resumen de todas las métricas de rendimiento "
"calculadas para cada combinación de pares de electrodos, y un informe "
"detallado del rendimiento de la configuración optimizada de electrodos. El "
"informe incluye la colocación de los electrodos, intensidades de corriente, "
"métricas de rendimiento, distribuciones de campo de alta frecuencia máxima "
"y TI, histogramas de dosis acumulativa y todos los gráficos generados en la "
"pestaña de análisis post-pro."

